title: Prices double that of a taxi
text: I downloaded the Uber app thinking I would get a better deal than taking a taxi. I arrived at Anchorage airport and went to the Uber app and put information in and it was quoted at $15, then when I went back into the app to get a ride it jumped to $40. So I took a taxi for $22. This happened 3 different times when I would check first to see how much it would cost and when I’d go to schedule the ride, it jumps to more than double. As we rode away in the taxi the Uber prices would drop back down again. I don’t trust Uber.
